commit.message:
Change abbreviation code for flood mode.

 * There's always space in the buffer for the whole message.
manpage: Clarify impact of waittime.
Cleaning up autoconf/automake a bit.

Add option to wait between reads of the pipe.

 * Lets messages build up, triggers flood handling more readily.
Change dates, versions for 0.2. (Closes #13). Remove INSTALL, add CHANGELOG.
Make flood detection configurable (Closes #12, closes #4)
Manage flood messages (not configurable)
Allocate the big buffers on the heap.
Handle messages which are split across buffer reads (Closes #14)
Add a buffer-cramming test to fix messages split across buffer boundaries.
Add flood detection algorithm (doesn't do anything yet)
Make attic; add the capacity dumper.
Put in proper name to credit fix on new libnotify version.
Remove duplicate declaration of wrfd in main (it's already a global)
Set hint for generic "append", not just Canonical extension.
Add ssuominengentoo to the AUTHORS file.

Fix to work with later libnotify versions (Closes #11)

 * Thanks to github user ssuominengentoo

Refine handling of pipe when there are no writers. (Closes #9).

 * Opening of write pipe is now non-fatal.
 * If pipe is ready but no data received, sleep before next iteration.
   Otherwise CPU is pegged.
Add .gitignore file that excludes autotools deritus
Add newlines at end of some files
Created new man page (Closes #6).

Removed TODO file in favor of issues in the tracker.

 * http://github.com/jtniehof/syslog-notify/issues

Added licensing and related files

 * Copyright notice in syslog-notify.c
 * GPL2 from http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl2.txt
 * AUTHORS list
 * INSTALL from automake 1.11
 * README and HACKING files for the project
Initial autoconfiscation
New TODO: keep messages from piling up (and becoming untimely)
Exit if can't write message (usually b/c X exited)
Filter HTML if server handles markup

Break line parsing out into its own function

 * Also create function to sanitize a line (just doesn't do it yet)
Initial commit
